[start section id="$final"]
Final Diagnosis
A.  Colon, sigmoid and rectum, low anterior resection:  Residual microscopic foci (3 tumor glands) of invasive grade 3 (of 4) adenocarcinoma in an ulcerated area measuring 2.1 x 1.4 x 1.1 cm. A single tumor gland is present outside the muscularis propria in perirectal fat.  Multiple (12) diverticula are also identified.  The proximal, distal, and radial margins are negative for tumor.  Multiple (31) regional lymph nodes are negative for tumor.

With available surgical materials, [AJCC ypT3N0] (7th edition, 2009).

Seen in consultation with Dr. Jackie M. Gaines.



[end section id="$final"]
[start section id="$gross"]

Gross Description
A.  Received fresh labeled ""sigmoid colon and rectum"" is a low anterior resection specimen consisting of 41.6 cm in length portion of sigmoid colon and rectum.  A 2.1 x 1.4 x 1.1 cm ulcerated ill-defined mass is present 2.5 cm from the distal mucosal resection margin and 1.6 cm from the radial margin.  Tumor perforation is absent.  Multiple (36) lymph nodes are identified within the perirectal fat.  Multiple (12) diverticula are also identified.  Representative sections are submitted.  Grossed by BROWN.



Frozen Sect-Intraop
A.  Colon, sigmoid and rectum, low anterior resection:  Residual microscopic foci of invasive adenocarcinoma extending into at least muscularis propria.  Margins negative.  HOLD to process lymph nodes and confirm.

Frozen section histologic interpretation performed by:  Jody L. Gaylord, M.D.





